.TH "trace_print_hex_seq" 9 "trace_print_hex_seq" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
trace_print_hex_seq \- print buffer as hex sequence
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "const char *" trace_print_hex_seq
.BI "(struct trace_seq *p "  ","
.BI "const unsigned char *buf "  ","
.BI "int buf_len "  ","
.BI "bool concatenate "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "p" 12
trace seq struct to write to
.IP "buf" 12
The buffer to print
.IP "buf_len" 12
Length of \fIbuf\fP in bytes
.IP "concatenate" 12
Print \fIbuf\fP as single hex string or with spacing
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Prints the passed buffer as a hex sequence either as a whole,
single hex string if \fIconcatenate\fP is true or with spacing after
each byte in case \fIconcatenate\fP is false.
